author: RICHARD BROOKS
title: RIALTO: Nighttime gunfire kills local man
text:
BY RICHARD BROOKS / STAFF WRITER
Published: Sept. 30, 2015 Updated: 8:54 p.m. RIALTO: Nighttime gunfire kills local man Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Related article Â» Nighttime gunfire in central Rialto killed a 24-year-old city resident, police say.
Keith Rice died at the scene of the 9 p.m. shooting Tuesday, Sept. 29, along the 100 block of West South Street, just west of Riverside Avenue and about a fifth of a mile southeast of the city's Metrolink station.
"The suspects possibly fired from a dark-colored vehicle as Rice was walking on the south sidewalk," Detective Sgt. Paul Stella said in a written statement released Wednesday afternoon. "It is unknown ... what prompted the shooting."
No arrests had been made.
Anyone with additional information may call Detective John Lopez at 909-820-2596.
